snippet.textDisplay: I always wanted to hear a Coke Studio version of Sayonee and now that I've heard it, with sadness I regret it. Minus Rahat on vocals, minus Salman Ahmad on lead guitars, it would've been a much better job done. Ali Noor's vocals really suited though. Comparatively with Junoon's original, yes this was a very poor attempt, a dull cover or bad improvisation if you may call it. Strings, what have you done to Coke Studio...
snippet.textOriginal: I always wanted to hear a Coke Studio version of Sayonee and now that I've heard it, with sadness I regret it. Minus Rahat on vocals, minus Salman Ahmad on lead guitars, it would've been a much better job done. Ali Noor's vocals really suited though. Comparatively with Junoon's original, yes this was a very poor attempt, a dull cover or bad improvisation if you may call it. Strings, what have you done to Coke Studio...
